Package com.intellij.util.containers

Class JBIterator<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.util.containers.JBIterator<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    TreeTraversal.It

    public abstract class JBIterator<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Iterator<E>
    Iterator that accumulates transformations and filters keeping its instance. So JBIterable#filter() and JBIterable#transform() preserve the underlying iterator API.

    Supported contracts:

    • Classic iterator: hasNext() / next()
    • Cursor: advance() / current()
    • One-time iterable: cursor()
    Implementors should provide nextImpl() method which can call stop()/skip().
    See Also:
    JBIterable.map(Function), JBIterable.filter(Condition), TreeTraversal.TracingIt
